RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 1 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 75. Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO 30% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 17 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less N ot Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RECKLESS AFFAIR settled off of the inside, advanced between horses through the second turn, tipped out four wide entering the stretch, dug in and was fully extended to narrowly prevail. JUST PRAISE was unhurried into stride, worked his way forward through traffic on the second bend, angled out entering the stretch to be clear, continued on well but was unable to best the determined winner. UP FOR THE CHANCE tracked three deep, launched a bold bid nearing the quarter pole, took over entering the stretch, but wilted during the drive and settled for the minor award. RAPA NUI settled toward the inside, shifted out nearing the furlong marker a finished with a belated improvement. CONRADO prompted the pace three wide through the second turn and gave way. HUNTIN' THE RUT set the pressured pace along the inside, disputed the issue to the final furlong and faded. DUDEWITHTHEDIAMOND went wide, moved up to make a mild bid on the second turn, but came up empty after six furlongs and dropped out.
